doc.after: Afriqiyah Airways was established in April 2001 and commenced scheduled services on 1 December 2001. It is wholly owned by the Libyan government and has 287 employees (at March 2007).[6] The airline started with Boeing 737-400 aircraft, but in 2003, an all-Airbus fleet was introduced.[citation needed] The Italian airline Blue Panorama jointly set up the airline with the Libyan government.[8]
